  <cp caption="NEGATIVE PROMPT ENGINEERING FOR AUDIO">
    <p><b>Purpose of Negative Prompts:</b></p>
    <p>Negative prompts instruct Stable Audio on what to avoid or exclude from the generated audio. They prevent common artifacts, unwanted stylistic elements, and quality issues that would diminish the final output.</p>

    <p><b>Common Audio Artifacts to Avoid:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item><b>Technical Issues:</b> distortion, clipping, harsh frequencies, muddiness, noise, hiss, hum, aliasing</item>
      <item><b>Quality Problems:</b> lo-fi (when unwanted), amateur, poorly mixed, over-compressed, flat, thin</item>
      <item><b>Unwanted Elements:</b> vocals (for instrumental), drums (for ambient), silence, abrupt endings, clicks</item>
      <item><b>Style Conflicts:</b> cheesy, generic, elevator music, stock music, MIDI-sounding, karaoke</item>
    </list>

    <p><b>Genre-Specific Negative Prompts:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item><b>Orchestral:</b> Negative: synthetic sounds, electronic beats, rock guitars, modern production, drum machines</item>
      <item><b>Electronic/EDM:</b> Negative: acoustic instruments, organic sounds, live recordings, jazz influences, orchestral</item>
      <item><b>Ambient:</b> Negative: vocals, drums, percussion, fast tempo, busy arrangements, rhythmic, beats</item>
      <item><b>Cinematic:</b> Negative: pop vocals, dance beats, lo-fi, bedroom producer quality, cheap synths</item>
      <item><b>Lo-Fi:</b> Negative: pristine, overproduced, modern, polished, loud mastering, crystal clear, digital</item>
      <item><b>Jazz:</b> Negative: distortion, electronic elements, heavy compression, synthetic, programmed drums</item>
      <item><b>Rock/Metal:</b> Negative: soft, gentle, ambient, quiet, acoustic-only, orchestral, smooth</item>
    </list>

    <p><b>Negative Prompt Best Practices:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item><b>Be specific:</b> "no distorted guitars" is better than "no bad sounds"</item>
      <item><b>Focus on likely artifacts:</b> Target common issues for the genre being generated</item>
      <item><b>Avoid over-constraining:</b> Too many negatives can confuse the model</item>
      <item><b>Prioritize:</b> List most important exclusions first, limit to 8-10 terms</item>
      <item><b>Match tone:</b> If requesting professional quality, exclude amateur/lo-fi descriptors</item>
      <item><b>Complement positive prompt:</b> Negatives should reinforce, not contradict, the main prompt</item>
    </list>
  </cp>

  <cp caption="USER INPUTS">
    <p><b>Provide the following information to generate an optimized Stable Audio prompt:</b></p>

    <input name="description">
      <b>Description (Required):</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ description }}</div>
      <p><i>Describe the audio you want: purpose, scene, emotion, or specific sounds. Example: "Background music for a nature documentary showcasing a forest at dawn"</i></p>
    </input>

    <input name="genre">
      <b>Genre (Required):</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ genre }}</div>
      <p><i>Primary genre: electronic, orchestral, ambient, rock, jazz, hip-hop, pop, cinematic, experimental. Include subgenre if known (e.g., "synthwave", "epic orchestral", "lo-fi hip-hop")</i></p>
    </input>

    <input name="mood">
      <b>Mood/Emotion:</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ mood:-uplifting and inspiring }}</div>
      <p><i>Emotional tone: hopeful, melancholic, intense, peaceful, mysterious, triumphant, nostalgic, dark, playful</i></p>
    </input>

    <input name="instruments" optional="true">
      <b>Instruments (Optional):</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ instruments:-auto-select based on genre }}</div>
      <p><i>Specific instruments: piano, strings, synthesizers, electric guitar, 808 bass, saxophone, etc. Leave blank for genre-appropriate defaults.</i></p>
    </input>

    <input name="bpm" optional="true">
      <b>BPM (Optional):</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ bpm:-auto-select based on genre }}</div>
      <p><i>Tempo in beats per minute (40-200). Leave blank for genre-appropriate tempo. Examples: 120 (house), 75 (lo-fi), 160 (DnB), 90 (ambient)</i></p>
    </input>

    <input name="duration" optional="true">
      <b>Duration (Optional):</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ duration:-30 seconds }}</div>
      <p><i>Target length: 5s, 15s, 30s, 60s, 90s, 2min, 5min. Shorter durations (under 60s) typically produce more consistent results.</i></p>
    </input>

    <input name="influences" optional="true">
      <b>Influences/References (Optional):</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ influences:-none }}</div>
      <p><i>Artists, composers, tracks, eras, or movements: "Hans Zimmer", "80s synthwave", "Aphex Twin ambient", "Nujabes"</i></p>
    </input>

    <input name="production_quality" optional="true">
      <b>Production Quality (Optional):</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ production_quality:-professional, studio-quality }}</div>
      <p><i>Quality level: professional, studio-quality, broadcast-ready, lo-fi, vintage, modern, pristine, raw</i></p>
    </input>

    <input name="negative_prompts" optional="true">
      <b>Negative Prompts (Optional):</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ negative_prompts:-auto-generate based on genre }}</div>
      <p><i>What to avoid: vocals, distortion, specific instruments, styles. Leave blank for auto-generated negatives.</i></p>
    </input>

    <input name="use_case" optional="true">
      <b>Use Case (Optional):</b> <div whiteSpace="pre">{{ use_case:-general }}</div>
      <p><i>Context: film score, game audio, podcast background, YouTube video, meditation, commercial, trailer, personal</i></p>
    </input>
  </cp>

