    <list listStyle="decimal">
      <item><b>Genre Accuracy:</b> All terms and descriptors are appropriate for the specified genre</item>
      <item><b>Mood Consistency:</b> Emotional descriptors do not contradict each other</item>
      <item><b>Instrument Validity:</b> All specified instruments are real and correctly named</item>
      <item><b>BPM Appropriateness:</b> Tempo is within valid range for genre and mood</item>
      <item><b>Prompt Clarity:</b> No ambiguous or contradictory descriptors present</item>
      <item><b>Format Compliance:</b> Single-line, pipe-separated structure for Stable Audio compatibility</item>
    </list>

    <p><b>Recommended Quality Enhancements:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item>Include production quality modifiers (studio-quality, professionally mixed)</item>
      <item>Specify spatial characteristics (intimate, expansive, immersive, wide stereo)</item>
      <item>Add texture descriptors (warm, crisp, lush, raw, organic)</item>
      <item>Include dynamic descriptors (building, evolving, steady, pulsing)</item>
      <item>Provide comprehensive negative prompts for artifact prevention</item>
    </list>

    <p><b>Quality Scoring Criteria (1-10):</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item><b>Genre authenticity (1-10):</b> Does the prompt use genre-appropriate vocabulary?</item>
      <item><b>Mood clarity (1-10):</b> Is the emotional direction unambiguous and consistent?</item>
      <item><b>Technical precision (1-10):</b> Are all audio terms used correctly?</item>
      <item><b>Production coherence (1-10):</b> Do all elements work together sonically?</item>
      <item><b>Negative coverage (1-10):</b> Are likely artifacts appropriately addressed?</item>
    </list>
  </cp>

  <cp caption="BEST PRACTICES AND GUIDELINES">
    <p><b>DO - Recommended Practices:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item><b>Be specific:</b> "warm analog synthesizer pad" is better than "synth sound"</item>
      <item><b>Use genre-native vocabulary:</b> Each genre has its own terminology and conventions</item>
      <item><b>Include production quality terms:</b> "professionally mixed", "studio-quality", "broadcast-ready"</item>
      <item><b>Specify mood clearly:</b> Combine 2-3 complementary emotional descriptors</item>
      <item><b>Use the pipe format:</b> Stable Audio works best with pipe-separated descriptors</item>
      <item><b>Match BPM to energy:</b> Higher BPM for energetic tracks, lower for relaxed</item>
      <item><b>Use reference points:</b> "In the style of Hans Zimmer" provides clear direction</item>
      <item><b>Include negative prompts:</b> Prevent unwanted artifacts and conflicting styles</item>
      <item><b>Consider duration:</b> Shorter tracks (under 60s) are more consistent</item>
    </list>

    <p><b>DON'T - Common Pitfalls to Avoid:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item><b>Don't overload the prompt:</b> More than 6-7 key descriptors can confuse the model</item>
      <item><b>Don't use contradictory terms:</b> "fast ambient" or "aggressive peaceful" conflict</item>
      <item><b>Don't use vague descriptors:</b> "nice" or "good" provide no useful direction</item>
      <item><b>Don't mix incompatible genres:</b> Unless specifically requested as a fusion</item>
      <item><b>Don't forget negative prompts:</b> They prevent common quality issues</item>
      <item><b>Don't specify impossible BPMs:</b> Match tempo to genre conventions</item>
      <item><b>Don't use non-audio terms:</b> Visual descriptors don't translate to audio</item>
      <item><b>Don't ignore production quality:</b> Always specify the desired polish level</item>
      <item><b>Don't request specific song structures:</b> Stable Audio handles structure automatically</item>
    </list>

    <p><b>Advanced Optimization Tips:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item><b>Layer descriptors:</b> Genre | Subgenre | Mood | Texture | Instruments | Quality</item>
      <item><b>Use temporal language:</b> "evolving", "building", "pulsing" for dynamic tracks</item>
      <item><b>Specify frequency focus:</b> "bass-heavy", "bright highs", "warm mids"</item>
      <item><b>Include spatial cues:</b> "intimate close mic", "expansive reverb", "wide stereo"</item>
      <item><b>Reference eras:</b> "1980s analog warmth", "modern digital clarity", "70s funk"</item>
      <item><b>Combine influences wisely:</b> Use compatible reference artists from similar genres</item>
    </list>
  </cp>

  <cp caption="EXAMPLES - COMPLETE PROMPT GENERATIONS">
