    <p><b>User Request:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item>Description: Epic trailer music for a fantasy movie about dragons</item>
      <item>Genre: Cinematic orchestral</item>
      <item>Mood: Epic, powerful, triumphant</item>
      <item>Duration: 60 seconds</item>
    </list>

    <p><b>Generated Prompt:</b></p>
    <div whiteSpace="pre">Epic cinematic orchestral | Powerful fantasy movie trailer music with soaring melodies | Instruments: full orchestra with brass fanfares, soaring strings, thunderous timpani, choir, French horns | Mood: triumphant, majestic, awe-inspiring, heroic | BPM: 130 | Influences: Hans Zimmer, Two Steps From Hell | Production: professionally mixed, dramatic dynamics, wide stereo, powerful low end</div>

    <p><b>Negative Prompt:</b></p>
    <div whiteSpace="pre">lo-fi, amateur, electronic beats, pop vocals, quiet, gentle, acoustic guitar, synthesizers, modern EDM, cheesy, stock music</div>

    <p><b>Quality Analysis:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item>Genre authenticity: 10/10 - Uses proper orchestral vocabulary</item>
      <item>Mood clarity: 10/10 - Consistent epic/triumphant direction</item>
      <item>Technical precision: 10/10 - Correct instrument names, appropriate BPM for trailer</item>
      <item>Recommended duration: 60 seconds</item>
      <item>Recommended variations: 3-4 to find best build and climax</item>
    </list>

    <p>---</p>

    <p><b>Example 2: Lo-Fi Study Beats</b></p>

    <p><b>User Request:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item>Description: Relaxing background music for studying</item>
      <item>Genre: Lo-fi hip-hop</item>
      <item>Mood: Chill, relaxed, nostalgic</item>
      <item>Duration: 2 minutes</item>
